FBIS4-68040 "jptot019__l94005" JPRS-TOT-94-019-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 4 May 1994 AFRICA TOGO Grenade Thrown at Restaurant; Six Foreigners Hurt Grenade Thrown at Restaurant; Six Foreigners Hurt European Restaurant AB0405095194 Libreville Africa No. 1 in French 0730 GMT 4 May 94 AB0405095194 Libreville Africa No. 1 French BFN [Excerpt] Violence is back on the agenda in Lome, Togo. Five Frenchmen and a Beninese were injured in the Togolese capital last night when a grenade thrown into a restaurant in the Be district exploded. The six victims are not in danger of death and the Togolese police have declined at this stage of their inquiry to speculate on the reasons behind the attack. The targeted restaurant belongs to a Frenchman and is known to be mostly patronized by Europeans. [passage omitted]
